cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning, specifically unsupervised part-of-speech (POS) induction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses word embeddings, which are a popular technique in machine learning and deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. Additionally, the paper uses multivariate Gaussian distributions, which are commonly used in neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with language, which can involve computer vision techniques such as optical character recognition (OCR), making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a less likely but still possible category.
